    <p class="sl">Recent Repairs</p>
    <h2>What appliance calls look like across Riverside County</h2>
    <div class="repairs-grid">
      <div class="repair-card"><span class="rtag">Temecula</span><h3>"Sub-Zero wine cellar not holding temp — winery event next week"</h3><p>Sub-Zero wine storage unit at a Temecula vineyard estate. Thermostat failure — drifting between 48°F and 65°F. OEM thermostat in stock. Stable at 55°F before we left.</p></div>
      <div class="repair-card"><span class="rtag">Murrieta</span><h3>"Samsung washer e2 error — new house, first appliance problem"</h3><p>Samsung front-load in a 2019 Murrieta build — drain hose had kinked behind the unit. Straightened hose, ran full cycle, error cleared. Homeowner's first appliance repair call.</p></div>
      <div class="repair-card"><span class="rtag">Corona</span><h3>"Refrigerator coils freezing over every few weeks"</h3><p>LG side-by-side with a defrost heater failure. Coils freezing solid on a 3-week cycle, plus external condenser debris from the pass wind. Fixed both — replaced defrost heater, cleaned external coils.</p></div>
      <div class="repair-card"><span class="rtag">Moreno Valley</span><h3>"Oven element cracked — cooking with one burner"</h3><p>Whirlpool range in a rental — bake element cracked from a decade of thermal cycling in extreme heat. Replaced element, tested at temperature. Tenant back to a full oven same day.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

